[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring module behavior**\n\nI’m thinking about how named modules interact with unnamed ones. It seems like a named module won’t read an unnamed module, but there could be exceptions. The `addReads` method might allow unnamed modules to add reads, which is intriguing. So, the invocation should happen. I’m pondering if automatic modules can read unnamed ones; it feels like they might, but I’m not entirely sure. I should clarify how these interactions work!\n\n**Exploring module-info generation**\n\nI need to enumerate packages from the classes directory to generate a module-info file. I consider using ModuleDescriptor.Builder in a custom ModuleFinder, but I’m not sure if classloader module access relies on the descriptor file. Maybe using a custom ModuleReference with descriptor to export packages could define a working layer. However, I think it might be easier to create a module-info.java source file with the module name and exports list, then compile it without running it. I could use JavaCompiler from JDK to address runtime, ensuring JVM coverage.\n\n**Refining directory setup**\n\nI'm thinking about how to create an effective directory setup. I believe I need to use the module finder and make sure to import ByteBuffer, Optional, Stream, and maybe HashSet or List. It might be simpler if I only fallback to an old jar. I wonder if we need to create a new jar at all or if removing those imports is a good idea. Editing might be the best way to go.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06417f7ca03b05b00169fc0dd43e3c8190997981ae8ff17144\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_A3zDov4rgvuIwz-LHQgJswNSL4Jj5B-9mJnK1sw7h-M8uYXjlgux41JE0GW8jtEX25M7pOySNamEh-HaZfopzteRKsqm7pGXKdX3QRmnoMl_jVhdmulr7S5hPywP5KGdOV6tev3ijSHBjo-CuBzjkef88e80-WByAyz2UfFIWKVab4XaetOD1ZnUlVixFRwnk51Tv_JAL3p6g_ThyKR0ujV9Ggd5Aud_lP-W1VXUtcGzcCZDzbzRossUcUhyzpoSMY1TAZpf-dUXEZpa